ideas for a year olds suprise party my little sister is and her bestest friend just turned she's gunna have a suprise party for her friend a sleepover there will be a small party of about year old girls any ideas on a theme and on what to do night time thanks i'll be tomorrow and on friday i'm having like girls sleepover we're going to make pizzas and rent a bunch of movies and stat up late we're all really fun and hiper so we pretty much make our own fun my mom also made some big fancy scavanger hunt but i don't know much about it they could also go to the movies or something like that another thing that's fun to do is write on pieces of paper something for your hair something for your feet something good to eat something for your eyes something funny then put each paper in an envelope with or dollars on one envelope put a number and on the other a later on divide the girls into teams each team gets an envelope take them to a local market or a target or something not very expensive each team has to buy what's on the list with their budget and not show the other team when everyone is done you take them back to the house keep the objects in the shopping bags and sit in a circle everyone draws a number out of a hat set one of the bags out of the way the person with the first number chooses something off the list of things they needed to buy someone who is not playing gets out the object they chose and gives it to her the second person can either steel that object or choose something else same with the third person do the same with the second bag at the end everyone should have two gifts they get to keep it was really fun when i played because we tried to get really wierd objects no one would think of so it was so funny to see what comes out of the bag like when we did it our feet object was a tiny baby pool that we said could be a foot jacussi we got alot of laughs off of that that's a really fun game cause u get a present and you get to go shopping Tag Wheel of Fortu